radiographic_examinations.findings: The bases of the lungs are clear other than minimal left basilar atelectasis. There is no focal consolidation, nodule, or pleural effusion. The liver is normal in shape and contour. No focal hepatic lesions, intra- or extra-hepatic biliary duct dilation, or renal lesions. The stomach and small bowel are normal without obstruction. The tip of the appendix is mildly enlarged measuring up to 9 mm with possible mild hyperenhancement of the wall and small amount of free fluid in the right lower quadrant.
